125.6	Mary_Magdalene	Mary Magdalene	Mary Magdalene (original Greek Μαρία ἡ Μαγδαληνή), or Mary of Magdala, was one of Jesus' most celebrated disciples, and the most important woman disciple in the movement of Jesus. Jesus cleansed her of "seven demons", conventionally interpreted as referring to complex illnesses. She is considered the "baby" of her family with her brother Lazarus of Bethany being the eldest and her sister Martha the middle child. She became Jesus' close friend and most prominent during his last days, being present at the cross after the male disciples (excepting John the Beloved) had fled, and at his burial. She was the first person to see Jesus after his Resurrection, according to both John 20 and .	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ec/Aveiro_March_2012-23.jpg/225px-Aveiro_March_2012-23.jpg
